  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "AI Engineer (Mobile Platform)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Technical direction: Mobile Platform</strong><br /><br />Leveraging Sony’s world-leading sensor technology, Pentas Vision is committed to driving the deep integration of AI and sensor capabilities. We are seeking a highly skilled AI Engineer to enhance sensor capabilities on mobile platforms and develop high-performance algorithms optimized for mobile devices.<br /><br /><strong>What you will be doing:</strong></p><ul><li>General encapsulation and optimization of the underlying framework; ensure the stability and efficiency of the underlying framework SDK, making it cross-platform and optimized for specific platforms.</li><li>Skilled in co-design of algorithms and software, with experience in optimizing computer vision algorithms on mobile platforms, including both traditional and deep learning approaches.</li><li>Responsible for the creation and optimization of engineering algorithm strategies; design and implementation of engineering algorithm strategies for industry businesses based on the algorithm SDK; optimize engineering algorithm strategies for different application scenarios.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>What you should have: </strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree or above in computer science, electronics, or related fields.</li><li>Proficiency in C/C++ development, solid programming skills, familiarity with common data structures and algorithms, object-oriented programming, and common architecture and design patterns.</li><li>Excellent networking and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Problem-solving, and analytical thinking.</li><li>Highly organized, diligent with great attention to detail.</li><li>Active listener, able to interpret and playback stakeholder requirements.</li><li>Highly driven and able to work individually and as part of a team.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Master's degree or equivalent experience in industry with in computer science, electronics, or related fields.</li><li>Preference for those familiar with GPU programming (OpenCL, Cuda), Linux programming and deep learning-related knowledge, image processing algorithms.</li><li>Experience in developing and deploying mobile SDKs, with prior work experience at Qualcomm and MTK are preferred.</li></ul>",
